01:16:41,881 --> 01:16:43,382
<i>into the four spot.</i>

1018
01:16:45,385 --> 01:16:49,305
We're losing tire pressure
in the right rear.

1019
01:16:49,306 --> 01:16:51,724
You couldn't beat me
straight up, could you, Wells?

1020
01:16:51,725 --> 01:16:52,975
Come on, come on!

1021
01:16:52,976 --> 01:16:54,526
Get off!
Give him a shot!

1022
01:16:54,527 --> 01:16:56,612
Binks: Yeah, watts,
smack him.

1023
01:16:56,613 --> 01:16:58,113
Hit him in the face.

1024
01:16:58,114 --> 01:17:00,115
Break it up.

1025
01:17:00,116 --> 01:17:01,150
Hey, you should
be disqualified.

1026
01:17:01,151 --> 01:17:04,453
Me? You rammed me
on purpose.

1027
01:17:04,454 --> 01:17:07,289
What are you trying to do...
Get yourself run out of the race?

1028
01:17:07,290 --> 01:17:08,791
I had him
and he jobbed me out of it.

1029
01:17:08,792 --> 01:17:10,042
So?

1030
01:17:10,043 --> 01:17:13,078
You gonna let it beat you?

1031
01:17:13,079 --> 01:17:14,959
Watts, Mr. Davies.
Should the engine be smoking?

1032
01:17:24,841 --> 01:17:28,060
I'll inform the starter
you'll be withdrawing from the race.

1033
01:17:28,061 --> 01:17:29,061
Yeah.

1034
01:17:29,062 --> 01:17:30,562
Sorry, son.
You did well.

1035
01:17:30,563 --> 01:17:32,064
Davies'll be
pulling outta the race.

1036
01:17:32,065 --> 01:17:33,515
Dad?

1037
01:17:33,516 --> 01:17:35,768
You ran a good race, watts.

1038
01:17:35,769 --> 01:17:39,271
Why is it that
anything that's good

1039
01:17:39,272 --> 01:17:40,273
always goes away?

1040
01:17:44,194 --> 01:17:46,529
Would you give us
a second, please?

1041
01:17:50,784 --> 01:17:53,952
Sometimes bad things
just happen, watts.

1042
01:17:53,953 --> 01:17:56,338
Sometimes there is no why.

1043
01:17:56,339 --> 01:17:58,341
Can I tell you something?

1044
01:18:00,343 --> 01:18:01,344
When your mother died...

1045
01:18:02,846 --> 01:18:06,132
That was the hardest thing
I ever had to go through.

1046
01:18:10,603 --> 01:18:12,104
These last four years...

1047
01:18:12,105 --> 01:18:16,609
It's been hard feeling anything
except sorry for myself.

1048
01:18:21,114 --> 01:18:25,617
I know that I haven't
always been there for you...

1049
01:18:25,618 --> 01:18:29,989
In ways that maybe
I could have.

1050
01:18:33,126 --> 01:18:35,128
But you showed me
something today, son.

1051
01:18:36,629 --> 01:18:38,464
The way you drove.

1052
01:18:41,751 --> 01:18:43,252
From here on out...

1053
01:18:45,255 --> 01:18:48,307
It's you and me, 100%.

1054
01:18:48,308 --> 01:18:49,676
Prove it, dad.

1055
01:18:51,845 --> 01:18:53,596
The comet?

1056
01:18:55,982 --> 01:18:57,483
Watts, that thing's
never even raced.

1057
01:18:57,484 --> 01:18:59,401
Never turned more than
two or three laps.

1058
01:18:59,402 --> 01:19:01,487
I don't even know
if the damn thing'll run.

1059
01:19:01,488 --> 01:19:02,238
It'll run.

1060
01:19:04,023 --> 01:19:05,858
You and mom built it.
It'll run.

1061
01:19:08,828 --> 01:19:09,829
Please?

1062
01:19:12,332 --> 01:19:14,199
Excuse me. Guys?

1063
01:19:14,200 --> 01:19:16,201
I heard your engine got cooked.

1064
01:19:16,202 --> 01:19:18,704
I have a spare engine
on my truck.

1065
01:19:18,705 --> 01:19:20,757
It's yours... if you want it.

1066
01:19:23,676 --> 01:19:25,677
I wanna beat
the best out on the track,

1067
01:19:25,678 --> 01:19:27,930
not back here.

1068
01:19:30,133 --> 01:19:32,468
We appreciate that.

1069
01:19:32,469 --> 01:19:35,305
But we're gonna be okay.

1070
01:19:40,643 --> 01:19:44,062
<i>All drivers need to reform,</i>
<i>watch the red flag</i>

1071
01:19:44,063 --> 01:19:46,064
<i>and prepare for</i>
<i>a running start.</i>

1072
01:19:46,065 --> 01:19:48,734
<i>Due to a short six-lap format</i>
<i>of this race,</i>

1073
01:19:48,735 --> 01:19:51,570
<i>there'll be no stoppage</i>
<i>until the checkered flag.</i>

1074
01:19:51,571 --> 01:19:53,572
<i>Green flag in one minute.</i>

1075
01:19:53,573 --> 01:19:56,992
What's the story, dad?

1076
01:19:56,993 --> 01:19:57,994
We'll get there.

1077
01:19:58,995 --> 01:20:00,746
Here. Get your helmet on.

1078
01:20:05,502 --> 01:20:07,753
( Revs engine repeatedly )

1079
01:20:07,754 --> 01:20:08,504
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

1080
01:20:17,063 --> 01:20:18,564
If she burps,

1081
01:20:18,565 --> 01:20:21,984
you're going to have
to adjust the carb through the chicane.

1082
01:20:21,985 --> 01:20:23,485
Any last-minute advice?

1083
01:20:23,486 --> 01:20:25,354
Yeah.

1084
01:20:25,355 --> 01:20:26,356
Go fast.

1085
01:20:31,945 --> 01:20:35,447
<i>It's up to the green flag</i>
<i>to decide who goes to Daytona.</i>

1086
01:20:35,448 --> 01:20:37,699
<i>Watts Davies has had</i>
<i>to change engines</i>

1087
01:20:37,700 --> 01:20:39,820
<i>due to that earlier collision</i>
<i>and now trails the pack.</i>

1088
01:20:43,873 --> 01:20:46,875
Okay, she hasn't run
in four years, buddy,

1089
01:20:46,876 --> 01:20:48,710
so let her breathe.

1090
01:20:48,711 --> 01:20:49,711
All right, dad, I got it.

1091
01:20:51,014 --> 01:20:53,633
<i>And here they go.</i>

1092
01:21:03,526 --> 01:21:04,943
Go, watts!

1093
01:21:04,944 --> 01:21:05,894
Yeah!

1094
01:21:07,530 --> 01:21:08,397
Get 'em, watts!

1095
01:21:15,121 --> 01:21:17,372
You feel that? Huh?

1096
01:21:17,373 --> 01:21:19,208
<i>That's a kick in the butt.</i>

1097
01:21:24,163 --> 01:21:26,748
<i>Rodney Wells moving toward</i>
<i>the head of the pack</i>

1098
01:21:26,749 --> 01:21:28,300
<i>while Scott McKenna</i>
<i>begins his battle back</i>

1099
01:21:28,301 --> 01:21:30,252
<i>from ninth position.</i>

1100
01:21:30,253 --> 01:21:32,337
<i>Lean it out, watts.</i>

1101
01:21:32,338 --> 01:21:34,306
Lean it out
on the back stretch.

1102
01:21:34,307 --> 01:21:35,307
I hear you, dad.

1103
01:21:35,308 --> 01:21:36,675
<i>Track's heating up.</i>

1104
01:21:36,676 --> 01:21:37,927
Watch your tire temperature.

1105
01:21:41,564 --> 01:21:43,566
<i>Rodney Wells takes the lead.</i>

1106
01:21:57,697 --> 01:21:59,698
Yeah!
Go, Rodney!

1107
01:21:59,699 --> 01:22:02,334
<i>The leader is</i>
<i>number 34 Rodney Wells.</i>

1108
01:22:02,335 --> 01:22:03,169
<i>Five laps left.</i>

1109
01:22:06,506 --> 01:22:08,291
<i>Another crash, this one</i>
<i>in turn number two.</i>

1110
01:22:20,970 --> 01:22:22,554
Good move, watts!

1111
01:22:22,555 --> 01:22:23,555
<i>Good move!</i>

1112
01:22:23,556 --> 01:22:24,273
I found my line.

1113
01:22:25,975 --> 01:22:29,561
<i>McKenna and Davies are each</i>
<i>making a big run in the field,</i>

1114
01:22:29,562 --> 01:22:31,397
<i>but watts has a long way to go.</i>

1115
01:22:51,918 --> 01:22:52,834
Go, watts!

1116
01:22:52,835 --> 01:22:54,086
<i>Lookin' good!</i>

1117
01:22:56,506 --> 01:22:58,891
<i>Four laps to go.</i>

1118
01:23:00,226 --> 01:23:02,311
I got McKenna in my sights now.

1119
01:23:27,253 --> 01:23:30,172
<i>The leaders are setting</i>
<i>an incredible pace.</i>

1120
01:23:30,173 --> 01:23:33,009
<i>The lap counts are going down,</i>
<i>the speed is coming up.</i>

1121
01:23:55,698 --> 01:23:57,533
Good move, watts.
Good move!

1122
01:23:58,951 --> 01:24:01,119
<i>Oh my, we've got a new leader.</i>

1123
01:24:01,120 --> 01:24:02,237
<i>It's watts Davies.</i>

1124
01:24:18,471 --> 01:24:21,139
<i>Scott McKenna</i>
<i>grabs back the lead,</i>

1125
01:24:21,140 --> 01:24:23,141
<i>but watts Davies</i>
<i>and Rodney Wells</i>

1126
01:24:23,142 --> 01:24:26,011
<i>are right there on his tail.</i>

1127
01:24:26,012 --> 01:24:27,480
<i>Two laps to go.</i>
<i>What an event!</i>

1128
01:24:39,075 --> 01:24:41,193
Okay, light bulb.
Here we go.

1129
01:24:41,194 --> 01:24:42,744
It's like you said, Rodney...

1130
01:24:42,745 --> 01:24:43,862
The rule is...

1131
01:24:47,700 --> 01:24:48,660
There ain't no rules.

1132
01:24:51,454 --> 01:24:54,039
<i>And Rodney Wells</i>
<i>is hard into the hay bales.</i>

1133
01:24:55,675 --> 01:24:58,511
( Rodney yelling )

1134
01:25:02,548 --> 01:25:04,433
<i>He looks okay.</i>

1135
01:25:04,434 --> 01:25:06,384
Get off!

1136
01:25:06,385 --> 01:25:09,638
This is the greatest day
of my life.

1137
01:25:10,973 --> 01:25:12,524
Tooms: Yeah, Rodney!

1138
01:25:12,525 --> 01:25:14,026
<i>Talk about getting tossed.</i>

1139
01:25:16,646 --> 01:25:18,864
<i>Coming down to the last lap.</i>

1140
01:25:18,865 --> 01:25:19,981
<i>Who's going to make it over?</i>

1141
01:25:19,982 --> 01:25:22,034
<i>We'll know</i>
<i>in exactly 40 seconds.</i>

1142
01:25:31,377 --> 01:25:32,044
Come on!

1143
01:26:06,529 --> 01:26:08,614
( Engine sputters,
then accelerates )

1144
01:26:20,543 --> 01:26:21,844
Come on!

1145
01:26:23,713 --> 01:26:24,714
Come on, watts!

1146
01:26:29,435 --> 01:26:31,053
Come on, watts!

1147
01:26:33,723 --> 01:26:35,524
<i>They come off the corner.</i>

1148
01:26:35,525 --> 01:26:36,558
<i>They're wheel to wheel.</i>

1149
01:26:36,559 --> 01:26:38,694
<i>They head for</i>
<i>the checkered flag.</i>

1150
01:26:52,625 --> 01:26:54,159
Yeah!!

1151
01:27:02,168 --> 01:27:03,419
Yeah!

1152
01:27:09,725 --> 01:27:11,309
Damn!

1153
01:27:11,310 --> 01:27:14,179
Where'd you learn
how to drive like that?

1154
01:27:14,180 --> 01:27:17,649
My dad taught me.
The best of the best.

1155
01:27:17,650 --> 01:27:25,650
♪ I opened up my eyes,
and I found beautiful ♪

1156
01:27:30,029 --> 01:27:35,533
♪ it opened up my life,
now I know beautiful ♪

1157
01:27:35,534 --> 01:27:37,369
♪ and how things should be ♪

1158
01:27:37,370 --> 01:27:40,956
♪ you are my beautiful,
beautiful to me ♪

1159
01:27:59,692 --> 01:28:02,193
You did it, buddy!
You did it.

1160
01:28:02,194 --> 01:28:03,028
We did it, dad.

1161
01:28:17,460 --> 01:28:19,462
You're the big winner!

1162
01:28:30,589 --> 01:28:34,142
♪ Beautiful ♪

1163
01:28:34,143 --> 01:28:39,481
♪ you are my beautiful ♪

1164
01:28:39,482 --> 01:28:41,267
♪ yeah, you're so beautiful ♪

